description:
Create derive macro for JsonSchema trait:

GENERATED TRAIT:
pub trait JsonSchema {
    fn schema_name() -> String;
    fn json_schema() -> serde_json::Value;
}

ATTRIBUTE SYNTAX:
#[derive(JsonSchema)]
struct User {
    /// User's display name
    #[schema(title = 'Display Name', example = 'John Doe')]
    name: String,

    #[schema(format = 'email')]
    email: String,

    #[schema(minimum = 0, maximum = 150)]
    age: i32,

    #[schema(nullable)]
    bio: Option<String>,
}

TYPE MAPPINGS:
- String -> {type: 'string'}
- i32/i64 -> {type: 'integer'}
- f32/f64 -> {type: 'number'}
- bool -> {type: 'boolean'}
- Vec<T> -> {type: 'array', items: T::json_schema()}
- Option<T> -> T::json_schema() with nullable: true
- HashMap -> {type: 'object', additionalProperties: V::json_schema()}
- Enum -> {enum: [...], type: 'string'} or oneOf for variants

DOCUMENTATION:
- Doc comments become 'description'
- #[schema(title = '...')] sets title
- #[schema(example = ...)] sets example

SCHEMA OUTPUT:
{
    'type': 'object',
    'title': 'User',
    'properties': {
        'name': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Display Name'},
        'email': {'type': 'string', 'format': 'email'},
        'age': {'type': 'integer', 'minimum': 0, 'maximum': 150},
        'bio': {'type': 'string', 'nullable': true}
    },
    'required': ['name', 'email', 'age']
}

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- All Rust types map to JSON Schema
- Documentation propagates
- Nested types generate refs
- Enum variants handled correctly

TEST REQUIREMENTS:
- Unit: Each type mapping
- Unit: Nested structs
- Unit: Enums (unit, tuple, struct variants)
- Unit: Optional fields
- Unit: Documentation extraction
- Validation: Against JSON Schema spec
